definition: generic name for hemp, flax etc/hemp or flax fiber for textile materials/sesame/CL:縷|缕[lu:3]/(of materials) rough or coarse/pocked/pitted/to have pins and needles or tingling/to feel numb

sentences.english: The goods we packed in new and sound jute bags each containing about 200 pounds.
sentences.chinese: 貨物是用堅固的新麻袋包裝的，每袋約重200磅。

sentences.english: There's just three burlap sacks in here. To which his partner replies…
sentences.chinese: 這裏只有三個麻袋，他的一個搭檔說。

sentences.english: The children huddled together on a pile of old sacks.
sentences.chinese: 孩子們在一堆舊麻袋上面擠成一團。

sentences.english: A woman sorts garlic to be filled in sacks in a shed.
sentences.chinese: 在一個工棚裏，一位婦女篩選大蒜並裝入麻袋裏。

sentences.english: Evidently, everyone carry his or her own sack of guilt and anger.
sentences.chinese: 顯然，每個人都有一麻袋的內疚和憤怒。

sentences.english: Three hundred and eighty sacks of mail take a lot of burning.
sentences.chinese: 三個一百八十麻袋信件花大量的燃燒。

sentences.english: The sack buyer was about to lock up.
sentences.chinese: 收購麻袋的人正要鎖門。

sentences.english: The goods were packed in gunny bags of 50kgs net each.
sentences.chinese: 貨物用麻袋包裝，每袋淨重50公斤。

sentences.english: In Single sound gunny bags or p. p. woven bags of 25 kilos net each.
sentences.chinese: 單層完整麻袋或塑編袋，每袋淨重25公斤。

sentences.english: Walnuts are to be packed in double gunny bags, each containing 50 kilos.
sentences.chinese: 花生要用雙層麻袋包裝，每袋裝50公斤。

sentences.english: He shifted the line over the sacks that covered his shoulders.
sentences.chinese: 他把釣絲從擱在他肩膀上的麻袋上換一換位置。

sentences.english: The green beans can be supplied in bulk or in gunny bags.
sentences.chinese: 青豆可以散裝，也可以用麻袋裝。

sentences.english: Puss-in-boots placed some lettuce in the sack and hid.
sentences.chinese: 穿靴貓在麻袋裏放了一些萵苣然後躲起來。

sentences.english: Walnutswill be packed in double gunny bags.
This balloon was a 38-foot diameter globe-shaped linen bag lined with 3 layers of paper.
sentences.chinese: 這個熱氣球是38英尺直徑全球形亞麻袋內襯3層紙。

sentences.english: Until my great-grandfather threw a sack over her head and carried her off.
sentences.chinese: 直到我的曾祖父用麻袋套住她的頭把她扛走。

definition: pouch/sack/bag/Budai (the Laughing Buddha)/Budai or Putai town in Chiayi county 嘉義縣|嘉义县[Jia1 yi4 xian4], west Taiwan
a basket carried on the back
full and bulging (of a pocket, pouch etc)
cloth pouch open in the middle, forming two bags/jacket worn for Chinese wrestling
